{{DISPLAYTITLE:''The Ring'' magazine Hall of Fame}} {{Use mdy dates|date=January 2016}} {{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}
'''''The Ring''''' '''magazine''' was established in 1922. In 1954 the magazine established its own boxing '''Hall of Fame''' and inducted 155 members before it was abandoned after the 1987 inductions. Boxing inductions continue through the [[International Boxing Hall of Fame]]. 141 members of the old ''[[The Ring (magazine)|The Ring]]'' magazine [[Hall of Fame]] have been elected to the International Boxing Hall of Fame since 1989. The 14 members who have yet to be elected to the International Boxing Hall of Fame are listed below, with their year of induction into ''The Ring''{{'s}} Boxing Hall of Fame:
'''Modern Group''' * 1973{{snds}}[[Gus Lesnevich]] * 1977{{snds}}[[Ceferino Garcia]] * 1977{{snds}}[[Yoshio Shirai]]
'''Old-Timers''' * 1976{{snds}}[[Jimmy Britt]] * 1978{{snds}}[[Peter Maher (boxer)|Peter Maher]] * 1982{{snds}}[[Harry Jeffra]]
'''Pioneers''' * 1962{{snds}}[[Ned Price]] * 1964{{snds}}[[Sam Collyer]] * 1968{{snds}}[[Jacob Hyer]] * 1971{{snds}}[[Nobby Clark (boxer)|Nobby Clark]] * 1972{{snds}}[[Tom Chandler (boxer)|Tom Chandler]] * 1973{{snds}}[[Paddy Ryan]] * 1985{{snds}}[[Thomas Jackling]]
'''Non-Participant''' * 1977{{snds}}[[Dan Daniel (sportswriter)]]
